# Bingo Number Generator — Game Rules

## Overview
A React-based bingo number caller that simulates the ball-drawing process for a standard 75-ball bingo game.

## Number Pool
- Numbers range from 1 to 75 (inclusive).
- Each number may only be called once per game session.
- Numbers are drawn in a random, non-repeating order.

## Display
- The current called number is shown prominently on screen.
- Previously called numbers are tracked and visible to players (e.g. as a list or board).
- The total count of numbers called so far is displayed (e.g. "12 / 75 called").

## Controls
- A "Call Number" button draws the next random number from the remaining pool.
- The button is disabled once all 75 numbers have been called.
- A "New Game" (or "Reset") button clears all called numbers and starts a fresh session.

## State
- On initial load (or after reset), all 75 numbers are available.
- Each press of "Call Number" removes one number from the available pool and adds it to the called list.
- No number can appear in both the available pool and the called list at the same time.
